I've been looking a bit more into this and I know a bit more about the issue. I'm still investigating, as it's still shows up and I need (and expect) the form to be pristine after the successful ajax submission. The problem seems to be in the resetFieldValidity method, the `rejected` attribute gets cleared, but not the `$message`, making it to show up again when the form is pristine.

```javascript
function resetFieldValidity(field) {
	field.rejectedListenerPos = field.$viewChangeListeners.push(function() {
		// changing the field the server complained about, resets the form into valid state
		field.$setValidity('rejected', true);
		field.$viewChangeListeners.splice(field.rejectedListenerPos, 1);
		delete field.rejectedListenerPos;
	}) - 1;
}
```

If I add a `field.$message = "";` after the `field.$setValidity*"rejected", true);`, then it seems to work. 

```javascript
function resetFieldValidity(field) {
	field.rejectedListenerPos = field.$viewChangeListeners.push(function() {
		// changing the field the server complained about, resets the form into valid state
		field.$setValidity('rejected', true);
		// clearing error message from previous validation
		field.$message = '';
		field.$viewChangeListeners.splice(field.rejectedListenerPos, 1);
		delete field.rejectedListenerPos;
	}) - 1;
}
```

