@sbma44 - I should clarify. The problem isn't adhering to the spec, it's interop with other tools. The GeoJSON from the geocoding API is 100% valid, a point which doesn't change but will be clarified in the updated GeoJSON spec. But many applications that work with GeoJSON will drop these, meaning that the user looses valuable info by choosing to use other tools. 

For example, opening the output of `mapbox geocoding` in QGIS doesn't show the place names or relevance scores as attributes. I could see the casual user run the command, open in their favorite app and when things don't look right, blaming this cli rather than their app. 

The suggested change would be optional and nothing more than a pragmatic way of dealing with the limitations of other tools. Maybe it's better as an external script? Or just documentation?

