@rmatev While I see your argument, I am not that keen on supporting it. It would only work with very simple options files, that do not include other option files.

@rmatev The issue with an exploding number of directories in the shared area is hopefully solved (it was a serious bug in Ganga causing this). Now, you should only get one directory for each prepared application. We could consider to implement some way to purge old shared areas (but this will then prevent you from resubmitting a job where you have done such a purge on).

@rob-c Why do you wan tto re-introduce pickling of options. In my mind it is a weakness in terms of that it is an extra step that is nor strictly required - and I am pretty sure that there are examples where pickling on the user node, followed by unpickling on the worker node is not fully reversible.

